HEADWORD: Subbrachiales
<hw>Sub*brach`i*a"les</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Sub-</er>, and <er>Brachial</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of soft-finned fishes in which the ventral fins are
situated beneath the pectorial fins, or nearly so.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subbrachian</ent>⟦br⟧
